# Website Auth Flow

Applies when editing website authentication (Login / Register / ResetPassword + Google social) under `website/`.

Authoritative guide: `docs/platforms/website/flow-auth.md`.

## Hard rules

### Routes and forms
- Auth routes are `/login`, `/register`, `/reset-password` on `BASIC`.
- Each auth page uses route-scoped `useShallowForm({ initProps: { api: API.FORMS.R("auth") } })`. Do not introduce mobile shared form identities on website.
- `publicRoutes` must include `Login`, `Register`, `ResetPassword`, and `Home`.

### Role-based home redirect (planned)
- Customer role home: `CustomerHome` → `/customer` on `CUSTOMER_MAIN`.
- All customer workspace paths use `customerRouter("/…")`.
- `getMyHomeIdentify` returns `CustomerHome` for `authedAs === "CUSTOMER"`, else `Home`.
- Authed on public routes → redirect to `CustomerHome`. Unauthed on `/customer/*` → redirect to `Home`.
- Post-login landing is owned by middleware after `auth.login` reload.
- Requires `/website/custom/start` auth payload under the `auth` key.

### Navigation
- Auth-internal links use typed `identify` via `useNav().push({ identify })` or `Link` with `href: { identify }`.
- Default auth logo links to `Home` via `Link` with `href: { identify: "Home" }` — no raw path strings.
- Full reload reserved for `auth.login` and `auth.logout` only.

### AuthPageShell layout
- Outer wrapper uses landing `Hero` section padding (`3rem 0 4rem`; desktop `5rem`/`6rem`) — not `minH` + vertical centering.
- Form card: white `cardBackground`, `shellBorder`, no shadow.
- Decorative corner brackets match `Hero.tsx` (navy top-right, orange bottom-left).

### Copy and i18n
- Auth copy in `ar.ts` and `en.ts` together.
- No placeholders on auth fields.

### Form injection and Loadable
- Keep `readOnly: !input.onChangeHandler` on `FormTextField`.
- No page-level `Loadable` during injection; submit button spinner only.

### Components
- Reusable primitives live in `ui/components/` with generic names (`Checkbox`, `SelectableCard`).
- Auth-specific wrappers stay in `ui/components/auth/` (`AuthNavLink`, `AuthSecondaryNavButton`).
- Primary submit uses `FormActionButton tone="primary"`; cross-auth CTAs use `tone="secondary"`.

### Register payload (shipped website)
- Email register sends `name`, `email`, `mobile`, `password` — matches backend `RegisterCustomerProps`.
- Success → `nav.push({ identify: "Login" })` (no token).
- Social register (planned) deletes email/password; uses cached `social` token.

### Post-success
- Login success → `auth.login` → cookie + reload.
- ResetPassword success → `nav.push({ identify: "Login" })`.

### Social auth (Google, planned)
- Google only; GIS via `SocialAuthHelpers.ts`.
- Forward ID token to `loginSocial` / `registerCustomerSocial`.
- Cache token in form values for retry; clear on provider switch.
- SSR-safe: invoke only from click handlers.

### Backend gating
- Auth subs gated `@sub(["website"], ["visitor"])` in `AuthRequester.ts`.
- `requesters.website.ts` lists every shipped auth sub under `visitor.auth`.
